The water isn't as cloudy as I thought it would be. Is
this also the effect of the slime? \n< Serena >
It may be possible to just live day by day, but what
about dealing with the slimes...? \n< Serena >
Hmmm... I can't seem to find any consistency in the
structure. Did they just expand the city without any
plan in mind? \n< Serena >
...No, that's not it. Are they repurposing an old
ruin? \n< Serena >
This sewage system of this scale is not even present
in the capital city. It cannot be provided for with
just one city's budget. \n< Serena >
I see, I see. So they keep Slimes in the parts that
are not suitable for sewage to balance the books. \n< Serena >
...This won't do. We came here to catch criminals. If
we keep dilly-dallying, we'll be caught off guard. \n< Serena >
...Hm!? \n< Serena >
What are you doing there, you! \n< Serena >
W-Why are there people here?! \n< ??? >
Stop right there! \n< Serena >
What incredible speed! Is that Guy who's running
away!? \n< Serena >
I won't let you escape, no matter what! \n< Serena >
Hmm... \n< Serena >
Is it because we're underground...? It feels strangely
chilly. \n< Serena >
But it doesn't smell as bad as I thought. Could it be
because the slime is decomposing all the filth? \n< Serena >
Not exactly a comfortable environment. Let's quickly
find this person called Guy. \n< Serena >
